<title>GERMANY: Hoechst details Q1 results.</title>
<headline>Hoechst details Q1 results.</headline>
<dateline>FRANKFURT 1997-05-05</dateline>
<text>
<p>Three months to March 31</p>
<p>(in millions of marks unless stated)</p>
<p>    Group pre-tax profit		     831     vs 1,245</p>
<p>    Group operating profit		   1,031   vs 1,320</p>
<p>    Group sales				  13,158  vs 12,977</p>
<p>    --domestic				   2,347   vs 2,442</p>
<p>    --abroad				     10,811  vs 10,535</p>
<p>Group operating return on sales (pct)7.8 pct vs 10.2 pct</p>
<p>    Group investment in fixed assets     821     vs 1,245</p>
<p>    Group personnel costs (excl pension  3,225   vs 3,262</p>
<p>provisions)</p>
<p>Group average workforce (headcount)  147,526 vs 160,146</p>
<p>Group workforce at March 31 (headcount)147,425 vs 159,817</p>
<p>    Parent sales				 3,029   vs 3,060</p>
<p>    --domestic				   1,318   vs 1,455</p>
<p>    --abroad				     1,711   vs 1,605</p>
<p>    Parent pre-tax profit		    405     vs 483</p>
<p>    Parent investment in fixed assets    124     vs 182</p>
<p>    Parent personnel costs (excl pension 887     vs 973</p>
<p>provisions)</p>
<p>Parent average workforce (headcount) 32,848  vs 37,421</p>
<p>Parent workforce at March 31 (headcount)32,758 vs 37,331</p>
<p>NOTE - Full name of the German chemicals group is Hoechst AG. The company said group pretax profit was up 9 percent on an adjusted basis. It also said that group operating profit fell 22 percent compared with the first quarter of 1996 but rose by 20 percent on an ajusted basis. The earnings adjustments are for the following factors:</p>
<p>1. The first quarter of 1997 contains 195 million marks in restructuring costs which was up 110 million marks from the year-earlier restructuring costs.</p>
<p>2. The first quarter of 1996 contained 300 million marks income from the sale of Hoechst's printing plate business and a 85 million-mark profit contribution from SGL Carbon in which Hoechst now no longer has a majority stake.</p>
<p>--Frankfurt Newsroom, +49 69 756525</p>
